```ts
export function asDefaultProps<P>(component: LooseComponentType<P>) {
    return <DP extends React.ComponentType<P>["defaultProps"]>
        (defaultProps: DP) => defaultProps;
}
```

`ComponentType<P>["defaultProps"]` is going to be `ComponentClass<P>["defaultProps"] | FunctionComponent<P>["defaultProps"]`, which will expand to `object | Partial<P>`. This will still work right now because we're not dealing with `FunctionComponent`'s problem, but it's more of a case of working by accident than working as intended.

Probably needs `<DP extends Partial<P>>`.

A similar problem is present with the `asPropTypes` function.

